TY  - JOUR
AU  - Constantinides, George M.
AU  - Ghosh, Anisha
T1  - Asset Pricing Tests with Long-run Risks in Consumption Growth
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/rar004
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 1
IS  - 1
SP  - 96
EP  - 136
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - We present a novel methodology for estimating/testing the Bansal and Yaron (2004) and related long-run risks (LRR) models based on the observation that the latent state variables are known functions of observables. The large standard error of the estimated elasticity of intertemporal substitution explains the controversy on its magnitude. The model requires higher persistence of consumption and dividend growth to explain the cross-section of returns than that observed in the data. The model matches the unconditional moments of consumption and dividend growth, but implies a higher risk-free rate and lower volatility of the price/dividend ratio, risk-free rate, and market return than those observed in the data. Contrary to the model implications, the conditional variance of the LRR variable fails to capture the large time variation in the equity premium.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/rar004
ER  - 



