TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hirshleifer, David
AU  - Lim, Sonya S.
AU  - Teoh, Siew Hong
T1  - Limited Investor Attention and Stock Market Misreactions to Accounting Information
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/rar002
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 1
IS  - 1
SP  - 35
EP  - 73
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - We provide a model in which a single psychological constraint, limited attention, explains both under- and overreaction to different earnings components. Investor neglect of earnings induces post-earnings announcement drift and the profit anomaly. Neglect of earnings components causes accrual and cash flow anomalies. The model offers empirical implications relating the strength of earnings-related anomalies to the forecasting power of current earnings-related information for future earnings, investor attentiveness, and the volatilities of and correlation between accruals and cash flows. We also show that, owing to attention costs, in equilibrium not all investors choose to attend to earnings or its components.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/rar002
ER  - 



